######################## Modules ############################

# A group of variables, functions and classes saved to a file is a module
# Every python file (.py) is module
# import keyword: If we want to use the members of the module in our program then we have to impor the module using import keyword.
# We can access the members of the other module by module_name.variable
# whenever we are using the module in our program, for that module a compiled file will be genegrated and stored on the hard-disk.
# We can rename the module with shorter-name while importing.
# import durgasoft as ds
# from .... import: we can access the members of the module directly without having to use the module-name, by using from ... import
# from durgasoft import *

